Comments.Message:
@Leva - fully understand your concerns and share them, too. There might be conceptsand ways to limit such misuse in the backend by e.g. having at least a certain number of the same changes reported before its committed into the db, or other approaches. I still feel that opening it up to the community can make a big help and bring it to another level - but agree, needs to be done thoughtfully.

However, maybe in the meantime it can be implemented to allow editing the location information in the local cache files, so I (and anyone who like to improves his data) can do those updates ?

@holymist - I wasn't aware that the two methodes of updating the item cache are complementary. I was under the impressing whatever you execute the last overwrite any previous information in the cache. So I'll give this a try and see how much this improves it for me. thanks for pointing this out.
